  "analyst_note": "CVE-2019-11510: Pre-auth arbitrary file read on Pulse Connect Secure. Affects 8.1Rx, 8.2Rx, 8.3Rx, and 9.0Rx before 9.0R3.4. Widely exploited in the wild \u2014 credentials and private keys are exposed at /etc/passwd and session files. The /dana-na/ path is characteristic of Pulse Secure portals. If present, this is a high-priority finding. Check the Server response header for 'Pulse-Secure'. For version confirmation, note that many Pulse deployments disable version disclosure.",
